from ocean currents research hope for tsunami early warning system the leopold leadership program skip to main content search this site the leopold leadership program about fellows news fellowship information resources fellows login home 2013 fellowship information all cohort reunion save the date june 19 21 2012 in this section 2012 newsletters newsletter archive from ocean currents research hope for tsunami early warning system john largier published on august 26 2011 photo millevache largier high frequency radar detected the march 11 tsunami in japan the first known observation of its kind made using radar john largier 2001 and his colleagues identified signals from the tsunami by analyzing radar data from their ocean currents research sites in california and northern japan this discovery raises hope for the development of new early warning systems using similar methods in ongoing studies we can now provide accurate estimates of the observation warning times for other regions eg the us east coast south east asia and the west coast of india the authors wrote tags disaster planning ocean currents tsunami 2012 leopold leadership program the stanford woods institute for the environment stanford university stanford ca 94305
